sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>(openshift-ingress)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KRBP as kube-rbac-proxy sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS (service-ca)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Notebook as Notebook Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP (loopback)

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over User,Notebook: Flow 1: Notebook Access (with kube-rbac-proxy authentication)
        User->>Gateway: HTTPS/443 (TLS 1.2+)<br/>No gateway-level auth
        Gateway->>KRBP: HTTPS/8443 (TLS service-ca)<br/>Bearer token forwarded
        KRBP->>K8sAPI: TokenReview (HTTPS/443)<br/>ServiceAccount token
        K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Token validation result
        KRBP->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview (HTTPS/443)<br/>Check GET on kubeflow.org/notebooks
        K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Authorization result
        KRBP->>Notebook: HTTP/8888 (loopback)<br/>X-Auth-Request-User/Groups headers
        Notebook-->>KRBP: Response
        KRBP-->>Gateway: HTTPS Response
        Gateway-->>User: HTTPS Response
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over User,Notebook: Flow 2: Notebook Access (without authentication)
        User->>Gateway: HTTPS/443 (TLS 1.2+)
        Gateway->>Notebook: HTTP/8888<br/>No auth
        Notebook-->>Gateway: Response
        Gateway-->>User: HTTPS Response
    end

    participant Controller as ODH Notebook Controller
    participant DSPA as DSPA CR
    participant IS as ImageStreams

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over Controller,K8sAPI: Flow 3: Notebook Reconciliation
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch Notebook CRs (HTTPS/443)
        K8sAPI-->>Controller: Notebook event
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create HTTPRoute (central namespace)
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ReferenceGrant (user namespace)
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy (user namespace)
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create/update ConfigMaps & Secrets
    end

    participant Webhook as NotebookWebhook<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS

    rect rgb(255, 230, 255)
        Note over K8sAPI,Webhook: Flow 4: Notebook Creation (Webhook)
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-notebook-v1<br/>HTTPS/443 (TLS service-ca)
        Webhook->>K8sAPI: Read ImageStreams (HTTPS/443)
        K8sAPI-->>Webhook: ImageStream data
        Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Notebook<br/>(sidecars, volumes, config injected)
    end
